# ============================================
# FOREIGNERS — MVP Sample Script
# ============================================
# This script demonstrates ALL MVP syntax features.
# Use it to test the parser and as a reference.

# --------------------------------------------
# FEATURE: Seed (deterministic randomness)
# --------------------------------------------

seed: 12345

# --------------------------------------------
# FEATURE: Location declaration
# --------------------------------------------

@rainbow-cafe

# --------------------------------------------
# FEATURE: Dialogue with emotion tags
# --------------------------------------------

mario: [[happy]] Hey Luigi! Great to see you.
luigi: [[neutral]] Hey Mario.

# --------------------------------------------
# FEATURE: Emotion stickiness
# (no tag = keep last emotion)
# --------------------------------------------

mario: How's it going?
mario: I've been meaning to catch up with you.

# Luigi is still neutral from before
luigi: Yeah, it's been a while.

# --------------------------------------------
# FEATURE: Changing emotions
# --------------------------------------------

mario: [[curious]] You seem quiet today. Everything okay?
luigi: [[sad]] Honestly? Not really.
mario: [[concerned]] What's wrong?

# --------------------------------------------
# FEATURE: Silent beats
# (character emotes but doesn't speak)
# --------------------------------------------

luigi: ...
luigi: [[sad]] I've just been thinking about things.

# --------------------------------------------
# FEATURE: Mid-line emotion changes
# (multiple [[tags]] in one line)
# --------------------------------------------

mario: [[sympathetic]] I'm here for you, buddy. [[warm]] Whatever it is.
luigi: [[grateful]] Thanks, Mario. [[sad]] It's about the bridge.
mario: [[confused]] The bridge? [[concerned]] What about it?

# --------------------------------------------
# FEATURE: Location change
# (triggers exposition shot + jingle)
# --------------------------------------------

@bridge

# --------------------------------------------
# FEATURE: Default emotion
# (first line without tag = neutral)
# This is Mario's first line at new location without explicit emotion
# But he had [[concerned]] before, so stickiness applies
# --------------------------------------------

mario: So this is where it happened?
luigi: [[somber]] Yeah. Right here.

# More silent beats
mario: ...
luigi: ...

# --------------------------------------------
# FEATURE: Emotional dialogue sequence
# --------------------------------------------

luigi: [[angry]] I still can't believe it happened.
luigi: [[sad]] I trusted them, you know?
mario: [[sympathetic]] I know you did.

luigi: [[bitter]] And for what? [[sad]] Nothing.

mario: [[gentle]] Hey. Look at me.
luigi: [[vulnerable]] ...

mario: [[warm]] You're not alone in this.
mario: [[determined]] We'll figure it out together.

luigi: [[touched]] ...
luigi: [[grateful]] [[happy]] Thanks, Mario. That means a lot.

# --------------------------------------------
# FEATURE: Return to original location
# --------------------------------------------

@rainbow-cafe

mario: [[happy]] Come on. Coffee's on me.
luigi: [[content]] Yeah. Yeah, I'd like that.

# Final exchange — testing stickiness through multiple lines
mario: You know what?
luigi: What?
mario: [[sincere]] You're a good brother, Luigi.
luigi: [[happy]] So are you, Mario.

# ============================================
# END OF SCRIPT
# ============================================
# 
# MVP SYNTAX DEMONSTRATED:
# - # comments
# - seed: NUMBER
# - @location
# - character: text
# - [[emotion]] tags
# - [[emotion1]] text [[emotion2]] more text (mid-line changes)
# - ... (silent beats)
# - emotion stickiness (persists until changed)
# - default emotion (neutral if never specified)
#
# ============================================

